cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes novel methods for quantifying uncertainties in natural language processing tasks using Bayesian deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the benefits of explicitly modeling uncertainties for enhancing model performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the experiments involve using convolutional and recurrent neural network models, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
